title: The Outlaw Josey Wales
actors: Clint Eastwood,Chief Dan George,Sondra Locke,Bill McKinney,John Vernon,Paula Trueman,Sam Bottoms,Geraldine Keams,Woodrow Parfrey,Joyce Jameson,Sheb Wooley,Royal Dano,Matt Clark,John Verros,Will Sampson,Len Lesser,Doug McGrath,John Russell,Charles Tyner,John Mitchum,Madeleine Taylor Holmes,John Quade,Clay Tanner,John Davis Chandler
summary: After avenging his family's brutal murder, Wales is pursued by a pack of soldiers. He prefers to travel alone, but ragtag outcasts are drawn to him - and Wales can't bring himself to leave them unprotected.

title: Muriel, or the Time of Return
actors: Delphine Seyrig,Jean-Pierre Kérien,Jean-Baptiste Thiérrée,Nita Klein,Claude Sainval,Laurence Badie,Martine Vatel,Philippe Laudenbach,Jean Champion,Jean Dasté,Julien Verdier,Nelly Borgeaud,Catherine de Seynes,Gaston Joly,Gérard Lorin,Françoise Bertin,Wanda Kérien,Jean-Jacques Lagarde,Jean-Paul Chevalier,Laure Paillette,Robert Bordenave,Yves Peneau,Yves Vincent
summary: A chamber drama about a widow and her son who live in an antique shop in Boulogne. The widow invites a man whom she loved twenty-two years earlier to visit. Her son is haunted by Muriel, a young woman whose death he may have caused while serving as a soldier in Algeria. As in Resnais' earlier films, memory is deflected, fragmented, enshrined, and imagined.
